    <item>
      <title>OSX as Syslog server</title>
      <link>http://www.ifconfig.it/hugo/post/osx-as-syslog-server/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 11 Jan 2011 16:23:10 &#43;0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://www.ifconfig.it/hugo/post/osx-as-syslog-server/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;How to keep track of logs of a Cisco router using OSX? Easy task!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Enable syslog listener on OSX:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://steen.lykking.dk/?p=45&#34;&gt;instructions here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;add this line to /etc/syslog.conf&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;local7.* /var/log/cisco.log&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;enable logging on the router:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;logging facility local7
! ip address of iMac
logging 10.0.0.1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;install the &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.apple.com/downloads/dashboard/status/syslogviewerwidget.html&#34;&gt;Syslog Widget&lt;/a&gt; and configure it to check file /var/log/cisco.log.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Use &lt;a href=&#34;http://geektool3.tynsoe.org/projects/geektool3&#34;&gt;GeekTool&lt;/a&gt; if you prefer to view logs on the desktop.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
